text: Yuliya Bogmatser (born 3 June 1984 in Zaporizhia) is a Ukrainian volleyball player. She played at the 2002 Women's Junior European Volleyball Championship, winning a silver medal, 2003 Women's European Volleyball Championship, and 2010 FIVB Women's World Championships. She was best setter in the Ukrainian Superliga in 2004/05 and in 2005/06. == References == Category:1984 births Category:Ukrainian volleyball players Category:Living people
